Data Gathering¶

  1. Directly download the WeRateDogs Twitter archive data (twitter_archive_enhanced.csv)

In [157]:
df_json = []
with open('tweet_json.txt' , 'r') as file:
    for line in file:
        data = json.loads(line)
        
        tweet_id = data['id']
        retweet_count = data['retweet_count']
        favorite_count = data['favorite_count']
        followers_count = data['user']['followers_count']
        friends_count = data['user']['friends_count']
        verified = data['user']['verified']
        
        df_json.append({'tweet_id' : tweet_id , 
                        'retweet_count' : retweet_count , 
                        'favorite_count' : favorite_count , 
                        'followers_count' : followers_count , 
                        'friends_count' : friends_count , 
                        'verified' : verified})

Quality issues¶

  1. tweet_id across all three tables should be "string" not "int"

  2. Null represented as None in the name, doggo, floofer, pupper and puppo columns of the twitter_archive table

  3. Timestamp is saved as object datatype instead of datetime in the twitter_archive table

  4. Missing Values in the twitter_archive table:

in_reply_to_status_id, in_reply_to_user_id have 78 entries instead of 2356

retweeted_status_id,retweeted_status_user_id and retweeted_status_timestamp have 181 entries instead of 2356

expanded_urls has 2297 entries instead of 2356

  1. 'text' column reveals that some tweets are not related to dogs and therefore some images are not for dogs

  2. some rows have multiple dog development categories, when it should be either just 1 or null

  3. melt p1,p2,p3.p1_conf,p2_conf....p3_dog into just 3 columns 'text' column in the twitter_archive table contains replies to tweets where only original tweets are to be considered

  4. some values in 'text' column contain links as well instead of just tweet content, create short_urls column, drop expanded_urls

Tidiness issues¶

  1. All the dog stages (doggo, floofer, pupper, puppo) should be merged into one column

  2. Information about the tweets are spread across three different files/dataframes. The files should be merged.

Cleaning Data¶

In this section, clean all of the issues you documented while assessing.

Note: Make a copy of the original data before cleaning. Cleaning includes merging individual pieces of data according to the rules of tidy data. The result should be a high-quality and tidy master pandas DataFrame (or DataFrames, if appropriate).

Quality issue 2, 6:¶

Null represented as None in the doggo, floofer, pupper and puppo columns of the twitter_archive table

melt p1,p2,p3.p1_conf,p2_conf....p3_dog into just 3 columns

Tidiness issue 1:¶

All the dog stages (doggo, floofer, pupper, puppo) should be merged into one column

Define¶

replace the None string in the doggo, floofer, pupper and puppo columns with Nan

create a new column and assign all the values from the above to it while dropping Nan

convert the new column datatype to categorical

drop the inital 4 columns

Code¶
In [191]:
dog_stage = ['doggo', 'floofer', 'pupper', 'puppo']

df_archive_clean['dog_stage'] = df_archive_clean[dog_stage].\
                                        apply(lambda x: ', '.join(x.dropna().astype(str)),axis =1)
df_archive_clean.dog_stage = df_archive_clean.dog_stage.replace('', np.nan).astype('category')

df_archive_clean = df_archive_clean.drop(columns = dog_stage, axis =1)

Tidiness issue 2:¶

more than one dataset is available; we need 1 dataset for proper analysis

Define¶

merge all the datasets using pd.merge to get one master dataset with all necessary information

Code¶
In [206]:
df_archive_clean = pd.merge(df_archive_clean, df_img_clean,
                            on=['tweet_id'], how='left')
In [207]:
master_archive = pd.merge(df_archive_clean, df_json_clean,
                            on=['tweet_id'])

Quality issue 5:¶

'text' column reveals that some tweets are not related to dogs and therefore some images are not for dogs

Define¶

from analysis earlier, it was observed that there were tweets implying that an image was not of a dog i.e tweets with 'we only rate dogs' as part of it's content. Filter and delete such tweets as they will not be useful to our analysis.

Code¶
In [209]:
not_dogs = master_archive[master_archive.text.str.contains('only rate dogs' , na = False)]

plt.xlabel('retweet_count')
plt.ylabel('favorite_count');

The retweets and likes increase and decrease simultaneously.
